  "prompt": "If I leave Aloe Vera gel on my face overnight and wash it in the morning, do I wash it with soap or just water? And can I put moisturizer after?",
  "response": "When washing off Aloe Vera gel in the morning after leaving it on overnight, you can generally just use **water**. Aloe Vera is water-soluble and should rinse off easily.\n\n*   **Why water is often enough:** Aloe Vera doesn't contain oils or heavy ingredients that require soap to remove. Using soap every morning can sometimes be drying, especially if you have sensitive skin.\n\n*   **When to consider a gentle cleanser:** If you feel like there's any residue or if you've also applied other products before the Aloe Vera (like a heavy serum), a very mild, gentle cleanser can be used.\n\n**After washing off the Aloe Vera, yes, you can and often should put on a moisturizer.**\n\n*   **Moisturizer Benefits:** Aloe Vera is hydrating, but it doesn't necessarily lock in moisture. A moisturizer will help to create a barrier and prevent water loss throughout the day.\n\n*   **Choose the Right Moisturizer:** Select a moisturizer that's appropriate for your skin type (e.g., lightweight for oily skin, richer for dry skin).\n\n**In summary:**\n\n1.  **Wash:** Rinse Aloe Vera off with water in the morning. If needed, use a very gentle cleanser.\n2.  **Moisturize:** Apply your usual moisturizer after washing.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Patch Test:** If you haven't used Aloe Vera on your face before, do a patch test on a small area of skin first to check for any allergic reactions.\n*   **Skin Sensitivity:** Pay attention to how your skin feels. If you experience any irritation, redness, or dryness, adjust your routine accordingly (e.g., use a milder cleanser, use Aloe Vera less frequently).\n*   **Quality of Aloe Vera:** Use pure, high-quality Aloe Vera gel. Avoid products with added alcohol or fragrance, as these can be irritating.\n\nIf you're using Aloe Vera for a specific skin condition or have sensitive skin, consulting with a dermatologist is always a good idea.\n",
